# Git and deploy workflow

## Remotes

- `origin` (GitHub: `jennyfan/prismaticminds`) — source of truth for branches and PRs
- `prod` (Namecheap: `ssh://namecheap/~/prismaticpractice.com`) — live site; tracks `main`

## Branch workflow

1. Do work on feature branches (especially `cursor/*` branches from Cursor).
2. Push feature branches to `origin` and merge into `main` on GitHub (PR or merge).
3. **Do not manually `git push prod main`** unless debugging deploy — merging to `main` on GitHub triggers automatic production deploy via GitHub Actions.

## Production deploy

- Trigger: push to `main` on GitHub (`.github/workflows/deploy-prod.yml`)
- Deploy action: GitHub Actions pushes `main` to the Namecheap git remote; the server post-receive hook checks out `main`.
- One-time setup: run `./scripts/setup-github-deploy.sh` and add the printed secret to GitHub repo settings.

## When helping with releases

- Prefer merging via GitHub PRs over local-only merges.
- After merge, confirm the "Deploy to production" GitHub Action succeeded before telling the user prod is live.
- Local manual fallback: `git checkout main && git pull origin main && git push prod main`
